This paper discusses the core techniques and recent developments in reinforcement learning, which are relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. Specifically, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are the most likely categories as they directly relate to the topic of the paper. Additionally, cs.RO (Robotics), cs.SY (Systems and Control), and cs.CV (Computer Vision) are also relevant as reinforcement learning is commonly used in these fields.
